<task>
<title> Final Project </title>

<shortdesc>This guide shows the user how to submit an assingment on Moodle.</shortdesc>

<taskbody>

<step>
<cmd>Proceed to wolfware.ncsu.edu to log in and hit the Log in box above the red arrow</cmd>
 <info>
                    <image href="one.png" placement="break"/>
                </info>
</step>

<step>
<cmd>Enter your Unity ID Login information.</cmd>
 <info>
                    <image href="two.png" placement="break"/>
                </info>
</step>

<context> 
Unity ID is a student email up until the @ and the password is the same as your email password.
</context>

<step>
<cmd>Choose a class and click on the Moodle logo, highlighted with the red box.</cmd>
 <info>
                    <image href="three.png" placement="break"/>
                </info>
</step>

<step>
<cmd>Scroll down to Assignments on the left-hand side of the screen and click on Assignments in the red box.</cmd> 
 <info>
                    <image href="four.png" placement="break"/>
                </info>
</step>

<substeps>
                    <substep>
<step>
<cmd>Choose and Assignment and click on a red link to submit it.</cmd> 
 <info>
                    <image href="five.png" placement="break"/>
                </info>
</substep>
                </substeps> 
              </step>

<info>
<note type="note">Note that some Assignments will say that the due date is off by a year or be completely off.</note> 
<image href="cupboards.png" placement="break"/>
</info>

<step>
<cmd>Please submit the assignment by the instructed due date the professor gave and ignore this overdue message.<cmd>
</step>

<step>
<cmd>Click "add submission"</cmd>
 <info>
                    <image href="six.png" placement="break"/>
                </info>
</step>

<step>
<choices>
<choice>  Either fill in the box next to Online text for your submission  </choice>
<choice>  or add a file submission. </choice>
 </choices>
  <info>
                    <image href="seven.png" placement="break"/>
                </info>
</step>

<step>
<cmd>To submit a file, click the first image to the right of the red arrow.</cmd>
</step>

<info>
<note type="note"> Note the maximum file size and chose appropriately.</note>
</info>

<step>
<cmd>Click "Choose File" and select a document.</cmd>
</step>

<step>
<cmd>Click "Upload this file" and choose a file.</cmd>
 <info>
                    <image href="eight.png" placement="break"/>
                </info>
</step>

<step>
<cmd>Click "Save changes".</cmd>
 <info>
                    <image href="nine.png" placement="break"/>
                </info>
</step>

<result>
Your screen will look like this with a submitted assignment:
 <info>
                    <image href="ten.png" placement="break"/>
                </info>
</result>

<info>
<note type="note">Note You can choose to edit or remove your submission up until the due date and time. </note>
</info>

</taskbody>

</task>
